    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Pale green, volatile oil obtained from the rinds of the lime fruit. Lime oil is normally prepared by steam distillation; its components are limonene and citral. It is used in flavoring, perfumes, insecticide, antiseptic, cleaning products, aromatherapy, and as a source of vitamin C. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
